# The correct reading here would seem to be -kalitā, which is accpted by both Norman and Cone (vol. 1 p. 653). This is exceedingly rare in Pali, but see http://sanskritdictionary.com/k%C4%81layate/159031/3
#. <br>
msgctxt "thag1.22:5.3"
msgid ""
"Te <span class=\"var\" title=\"sītavātakadditakalitā (bj) | sītavātakalitā ("
